GHANA will be missing a number of big name players when they face Bafana Bafana in next month. The Black Stars will host Molefi Ntsekiâ€™s side in Accra on the 14 November in the Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers Group C opener without a few of their star players. Former captain and all time goal scorer Asamoah Gyan, defender John Boye, Newcastle United winger Christian Atsu and Inter Milan left-back Kwadyo Asamoah have all been ruled out through injury. However, the team does still looks very strong. The Back Stars team is headlined by Maritzburg United goalkeeper Richard Ofori and Spanish-based midfielder Thomas Partey of Atletico Madrid. The Ayew brothers, Jordan and capatin Andre, have also been included. Bafana will need to keep a close eye on the younger of the Ayew brothers, Joradan, as he has been in fine form for his club Crystal Palace in England. The 28-year-old has scored four goals in nine matches thus far in the English Premier League, one of them coming in a 2-2 draw with Arsenal on Sunday. This is the list of the players below called by Coach Kwesi Appiah squad: GOALKEEPERS: Richard Ofori (Maritzburg FC, South Africa), Felix Annan (Asante Kotoko, Ghana), Razak Abalora (Azam FC, Tanzania) DEFENDERS: Andy Yiadom (Reading, England), Harrison Afful (Columbus Crew, USA), Lumor Agbenyenu (Real Mallorca, Spain), Joseph Aidoo (Celta Vigo, Spain), Joseph Aidoo (Celta Vigo, Spain), Kassim Nuhu (Fortuna Dusseldorf, Germany), Nicholas Opoku (Udinese, Italy), Mohammed Salisu (Real Valladolid, Spain) MIDFIELDERS: Samuel Owusu (Al Fahya, Saudi Arabia), Thomas Partey (Atletico Madrid, Spain), Alfred Duncan (Sassuolo, Italy), Mubarak Wakaso (Deportivo Alaves, Spain), Iddrisu Baba (Real Mallorca, Spain), Christopher Antwi-Adjei (SC Paderborn, Germany) FORWARD: Andre Ayew (Swansea, England), Mohammed Kudus (FC Nordsjaelland, Denmark), Emmanuel Boateng (Dalian Yifang, China), Jordan Ayew (Crystal Palace, England), Torric Jibril (TP Mazembe, DR Congo), Shafiu Mumuni (Asha